webpackJsonp([0xc99e8c873b7f],{689:function(e,t){e.exports={data:{allMarkdownRemark:{edges:[{node:{id:"C:/Users/slyon/Documents/GitHub/rots-site/src/pages/docs/skills/leadership.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:"<p>Characters who have high leadership will find that so long as they\nshow no signs of fear, that their followers will also stand firm in\nthe face of their enemies. </p>\n<p>For now, only common orcs can learn this skill.</p>",frontmatter:{title:"LEADERSHIP",syntax:"N/A (automatic effect)",group:"N/A",level:0,offensive:null}}},{node:{id:"C:/Users/slyon/Documents/GitHub/rots-site/src/pages/docs/skills/cover.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:"<p>You will attempt to cover all the tracks in this room.  If you\nsucceed, the tracks will look much older, or may not be seen at all.</p>\n<p>You need to specialize in stealth to learn this skill.</p>",frontmatter:{title:"COVER",syntax:"cover",group:"Ranger",level:0,offensive:"No"}}},{node:{id:"C:/Users/slyon/Documents/GitHub/rots-site/src/pages/docs/skills/ride.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:"<p>Riding will mount one upon chosen target, if the target is a mount\nmob.  Without the use of this skill, riding will not benefit one much,\nand might even be worse than walking normally.  Rangers who know how\nto deal with animals will also find riding easier.\nTyping just 'ride' while a mount is following you will have you ride\nthe mount.</p>\n<p> ride                      - rides the first following mount.</p>\n<p> ride target             - rides target, if target is a mount mob.</p>\n<p> dismount                  - dismounts, mount starts following you.</p>\n<p>lose target             - \"loses\" target following mob/person.</p>",frontmatter:{title:"RIDE",syntax:"ride <target> / ride",group:"Ranger",level:0,offensive:"No"}}},{node:{id:"C:/Users/slyon/Documents/GitHub/rots-site/src/pages/docs/skills/search.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:"<p>Searching in a room without a chosen target will search for\nhidden people in the room, uncovering friends and enemies alike.\nWith a chosen direction, it will search in the direction for a\nhidden exit.  The success of a search depends primarily upon the\namount of experience the searcher has with the search skill;\nhowever, it is also heavily based on the searcher's awareness and\nintelligence.  </p>\n<p>If you fail to uncover a hidden character in your room after\nsearching it, that character's hide will be less effective for\nevading further detection.</p>\n<p>Examples:</p>\n<p>search north</p>\n<p>searches for a hidden exit to the north.</p>\n<p>search</p>\n<p>searches for hidden characters in the room.</p>",frontmatter:{title:"SEARCH",syntax:"search / search <direction>",group:"Ranger",level:0,offensive:"No"}}},{node:{id:"C:/Users/slyon/Documents/GitHub/rots-site/src/pages/docs/skills/stalk.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:"<p>The skill lets you move between rooms without leaving tracks.</p>\n<p>Side note: you can try to stalk without knowing the skill. It will result\nin funny results.</p>\n<p>You need to specialize in stealth to learn this skill.</p>",frontmatter:{title:"STALK",syntax:"stalk <direction>",group:"Ranger",level:0,offensive:"No"}}},{node:{id:"C:/Users/slyon/Documents/GitHub/rots-site/src/pages/docs/skills/track.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:"<p>Tracking will have you attempt to find tracks of things that have passed\nthrough the room you are in.  The command 'track', without a target, will\nattempt to show all the tracks found in the room.  Tracking a chosen target\nwill attempt to show any tracks of the target that are in the room.</p>\n<p>Tracks do disappear over time.  Tracks can be more or less visible depending\non the weather and the terrain.</p>\n<p>Also, one can use the command 'hunt'.  Based on one's tracking ability, they\ncan attempt to see the tracks in a room upon 'look'ing in and entering rooms.\nThe chance to successfully see tracks while hunting is less than while\ntracking normally, and one will only find fresh tracks.  Also, there is a\nsmall delay associated with hunting, which happens after looking/entering\na room.</p>\n<p> track                  - searches for tracks in the room.</p>\n<p> track target         - searches for tracks of target in the room.</p>\n<p> hunt                   - Toggles hunting on and off.</p>",frontmatter:{title:"TRACK",syntax:"track / track <target> / hunt",group:"Ranger",level:0,offensive:"No"}}},{node:{id:"C:/Users/slyon/Documents/GitHub/rots-site/src/pages/docs/skills/whistle.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:"<p>If you have a pet and you got separated, the whistle will summon it\nback to you. Of course, you can be heard only from reasonable distance,\nand may need to whistle more than once.</p>\n<p>You need to specialize in animals to learn this skill.</p>\n<p>Common orcs can whistle to gather their recruits without learning\nthe skill.</p>",frontmatter:{title:"WHISTLE",syntax:"whistle",group:"Ranger",level:0,offensive:"No"}}},{node:{id:"C:/Users/slyon/Documents/GitHub/rots-site/src/pages/docs/skills/archery.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:"<p>The Archery skill allows you to utilize a bow and arrow. The chance\nof having a successful shot is determined by the attacker's archery skill,\naccuracy skill, and ranger level. The attack must also be wielding a bow\nor crossbow, have a quiver on his/her back, arrows inside the quiver, and\nwield the bow/crossbow with both hands. </p>",frontmatter:{title:"ARCHERY",syntax:"shoot <target>",group:"Ranger",level:1,offensive:"Yes"}}},{node:{id:"C:/Users/slyon/Documents/GitHub/rots-site/src/pages/docs/skills/awareness.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:"<p>The awareness skill heightens one's senses, helping them to be\naware of hiding life and notice oncoming ambushes.  A ranger's\nawareness is dependent on many factors, including: proficiency\nas a ranger, proficiency in the awareness skill, specialization,\nintelligence, and race.</p>",frontmatter:{title:"AWARENESS",syntax:"N/A (automatic effect)",group:"Ranger",level:1,offensive:"No"}}},{node:{id:"C:/Users/slyon/Documents/GitHub/rots-site/src/pages/docs/skills/calm.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:"<p>The Calm skill allows one to calm animals, stopping them from\naggressive action for a period of time, and making them easier\nto tame.</p>",frontmatter:{title:"CALM",syntax:"calm <target>",group:"Ranger",level:1,offensive:"No"}}},{node:{id:"C:/Users/slyon/Documents/GitHub/rots-site/src/pages/docs/skills/dodge.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:"<p>The Dodge skill improves your dodging bonus (DB).  Effectiveness\ndepends on your ranger level.</p>",frontmatter:{title:"DODGE",syntax:"N/A (automatic effect)",group:"Ranger",level:1,offensive:"No"}}},{node:{id:"C:/Users/slyon/Documents/GitHub/rots-site/src/pages/docs/skills/picklock.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:"<p>The Pick Lock skill allows one to try and pick a lock, unlocking whatever\nwas chosen as a target if successful.  Not all locks can be picked.</p>\n<p>pick <door>          - attempts to pick the lock of a locked target door.</p>\n<p>pick <container>     - attempts to pick the lock of a locked target container.</p>",frontmatter:{title:"PICK LOCK",syntax:"pick <door/container>",group:"Ranger",level:1,offensive:"No"}}},{node:{id:"C:/Users/slyon/Documents/GitHub/rots-site/src/pages/docs/skills/swim.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:'<p>Swimming allows one to enter water-filled rooms without the aid of a boat.\nTo enable the skill, one must "set swim on".</p>',frontmatter:{title:"SWIM",syntax:"N/A (automatic effect)",group:"Ranger",level:1,offensive:"No"}}},{node:{id:"C:/Users/slyon/Documents/GitHub/rots-site/src/pages/docs/skills/hide.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:"<p>The hide skill allows one to hide from others.  While hidden,\nthere is a chance people will not notice you, based on your\nhide skill, ranger level, whether you entered the room with a\nsuccessful sneak, stealth, and terrain, versus the other player\nor mob's awareness.  It is skill versus skill; anyone may\nattempt to hide, as well as anyone can possibly see a hidden\nplayer.  While hidden, most actions will cause you to reveal\nyourself.</p>\n<p>You may also choose to specify the WELL option when hiding.\nBy using HIDE WELL, you will take a substantially greater care\nin choosing your hiding spot, resulting in a long wait and\nenhanced concealment.</p>",frontmatter:{title:"HIDE",syntax:"hide / hide well",group:"Ranger",level:2,offensive:"No"}}},{node:{id:"C:/Users/slyon/Documents/GitHub/rots-site/src/pages/docs/skills/stealth.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:"<p>The stealth skill increases one's ability to perform skills\nthat require an element of surprise or concealment, such as:\nhiding, sneaking, riposting and ambushing.  To become a master\nof stealth, however, requires a rather hefty sacrifice of\nphysical constitution.</p>",frontmatter:{title:"STEALTH",syntax:"N/A (automatic effect)",group:"Ranger",level:2,offensive:"No"}}},{node:{id:"C:/Users/slyon/Documents/GitHub/rots-site/src/pages/docs/skills/tame.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:"<p>The Tame skill allows one to tame most animals.  A tamed animal\nwill follow you, and obey your commands.  The animals you can tame\nare determined by your tame skill, ranger level, whether the animal\nhas been calmed, and whether you have any animals tamed already.\nNote that because of the way this skill is coded, some things\nwhich are actually animals are untameable as of now.</p>",frontmatter:{title:"TAME",syntax:"tame <target>",group:"Ranger",level:2,offensive:"No"}}},{node:{id:"C:/Users/slyon/Documents/GitHub/rots-site/src/pages/docs/skills/fastattack.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:"<p>The Fast Attack skill increases one's attack speed under certain\nconditions.  The increase in speed depends on the percent learned in\nthe skill and the weight of the wielded weapon.  Effect while wielding\na heavy weapon will be low to none, while it could be quite a bit with\na light weight weapon.</p>",frontmatter:{title:"FAST ATTACK",syntax:"N/A (automatic effect)",group:"Ranger",level:3,offensive:"No"}}},{node:{id:"C:/Users/slyon/Documents/GitHub/rots-site/src/pages/docs/skills/gather.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:'<p>The Gather Herbs skill allows a ranger to find useful materials on the land\n(not only herbs). "Gather food" lets one attempt to find some edible roots and\nberries, and "gather light" finds something that burns well. "Gather energy"\nand "gather healing" puts you in a mode of gathering useful herbs that help\nyou replenish moves or hit points. "Gather bow" will find some twigs and\nbranches to fashion into a crude bow. "Gather arrow" will search the room for\nitems that you can make into a crude arrow. Fish" command is a version of "gather\nfood", that allows one to fish, while holding a fishing pole and riding a\nboat, if in a water room. The outcome of the gathering is strongly affected by\nthe terrain in which one is gathering.</p>\n<p>gather food     - attempts to gather food from current location.\nfish            - attempts to fish from current location.</p>',frontmatter:{title:"GATHER",syntax:"gather [food/energy/healing/light/bow/arrow] OR fish",group:"Ranger",level:5,offensive:"No"}}},{node:{id:"C:/Users/slyon/Documents/GitHub/rots-site/src/pages/docs/skills/sneak.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:"<p>Sneaking allows one to move between rooms without anyone taking\nnotice to the sneaker's entrance or exit.  When someone enters\na room without being noticed, they are effectively hidden - but\nvery poorly.  However, since the sneaker did not forfeit his\nelement of surprise by entering haphazardly, he receives quite\na formidable bonus to any stealth* related abilities that he may\nperform while still unnoticed.  Since the moving character is\npaying far more attention to his movements than in casual motion,\nthere is a small delay associated with any movement while sneak\nis enabled. </p>\n<p>A successful discreet passage from one room to the next depends\non the sneaker's knowledge of the sneak skill and their stealth.</p>\n<p>To toggle sneak on or off, simply type 'sneak'</p>",frontmatter:{title:"SNEAK",syntax:"sneak",group:"Ranger",level:5,offensive:"No"}}},{node:{id:"C:/Users/slyon/Documents/GitHub/rots-site/src/pages/docs/skills/ambush.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:"<p>Ambush is the favored attack of rangers; and it can be used with\nany weapon type.  The chance of performing a successful ambush is\ndetermined by the attacker's ambush skill, stealth, encumbrance\nand ranger level.</p>\n<p>A successful ambush removes a percentage of target's health based\non the factors stated above for percentage chance; additionally,\nthe damage depends upon the damage of the weapon the ranger is\nwielding and the encumbrance of the victim of the ambush.  It\nshould be noted that although heavy weapons increase the power of\nan ambush, they increase the challenge of landing an ambush\nconsiderably.  In addition to damaging the victim, the surprise\nand force of the ambush generally leaves the victim rather\nconfused, making it more difficult for him to parry.</p>\n<p>ambush wolf</p>\n<p>The trap ability allows rangers to prepare an ambush for a target\nnot yet present.  When the target enters the room where a ranger\nhas laid a trap, the ranger will instantly spring his trap, causing\nthe victim a good deal of damage.  Additionally, due to the nature\nof surprising a victim with such force and pain, the victim of a\nsuccessful trap will become stunned for a short period of time,\nwhile it tries to make sense of what is happening around it.</p>\n<p>You may choose to trap N.target; if you choose to do this, then\nyou will spring your trap when the Nth number of that target has\nentered the trapped room.</p>\n<p>trap warg\ntrap 2.orc</p>",frontmatter:{title:"AMBUSH",syntax:"ambush <target> OR trap <target>",group:"Ranger",level:6,offensive:"Yes"}}},{node:{id:"C:/Users/slyon/Documents/GitHub/rots-site/src/pages/docs/skills/travelling.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:"<p>Experts in travelling are told to be able to run days and nights with no\nrest and travel great distances in amazingly little amount of times.</p>",frontmatter:{title:"TRAVELLING",syntax:"N/A (automatic effect)",group:"Ranger",level:6,offensive:"No"}}},{node:{id:"C:/Users/slyon/Documents/GitHub/rots-site/src/pages/docs/skills/animals.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:"<p>The Animals skill is one's ability to communicate with animals.\nThe skill increases a person's effectiveness with the tame and calm\nskills, as well as with ride.</p>",frontmatter:{title:"ANIMALS",syntax:"N/A (automatic effect)",group:"Ranger",level:10,offensive:"No"}}},{node:{id:"C:/Users/slyon/Documents/GitHub/rots-site/src/pages/docs/skills/accuracy.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:"<p>The Accuracy skill allows you to shoot your bow/crossbow with better\naccuracy and find weaknesses in your enemy's armour. If successful, it\nwill allow an arrow to bypass your enemy's armour absorption.</p>",frontmatter:{title:"ACCURACY",syntax:"N/A (automatic effect)",group:"Ranger",level:15,offensive:"No"}}},{node:{id:"C:/Users/slyon/Documents/GitHub/rots-site/src/pages/docs/skills/riposte.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:"<p>Riposte is a high level skill which gives rangers the chance of an\nautomatic hit when they parry an attack.  Its success depends on the\nranger level of the player, their stealth, riposte skill and dexterity.</p>",frontmatter:{title:"RIPOSTE",syntax:"N/A (automatic effect)",group:"Ranger",level:20,offensive:"Yes"}}},{node:{id:"C:/Users/slyon/Documents/GitHub/rots-site/src/pages/docs/skills/parry.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:"<p>The Parry skill improves your parry bonus (PB).  Effectiveness\ndepends on your warrior level.</p>",frontmatter:{title:"PARRY",syntax:"N/A (automatic effect)",group:"Warrior",level:0,offensive:"No"}}},{node:{id:"C:/Users/slyon/Documents/GitHub/rots-site/src/pages/docs/skills/weapontypes.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:'<p>The following weapon skills are available: slashing, concussion, spears,\npiercing, axes, and whips/flails.  It\'s not trivial to determine which weapon\nis better (though comparing can give you some idea), or which good weapon you\nwill find in your adventures. Slashing weapons are most common, so many people\nlearn how to use only slashing weapons. If you want to know how to use any type\nof weapons, consider learning "weapon mastery".</p>',frontmatter:{title:"WEAPON TYPES SLASHING CONCUSSION POLEARMS PIERCING SPEARS AXES WHIPS/FLAILS",syntax:"N/A (automatic effect)",group:"Warrior",level:0,offensive:"No"}}},{node:{id:"C:/Users/slyon/Documents/GitHub/rots-site/src/pages/docs/skills/swing.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:"<p>Those specialized in Wild fighting can learn this move to damage\ntheir opponents. More effective than kick, this skill is unreliable\nand can hurt your friends sometimes.</p>\n<p>You need to specialize in wild fighting to learn this skill.</p>",frontmatter:{title:"WILD SWING",syntax:"swing <target>",group:"Warrior",level:0,offensive:"Yes"}}},{node:{id:"C:/Users/slyon/Documents/GitHub/rots-site/src/pages/docs/skills/naturalattacks.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:"<p>The following skills helps with using claws to successfully attack opponents. Damage is based off your strength score, warrior level, and character level.</p>",frontmatter:{title:"NATURAL ATTACKS",syntax:"",group:"Warrior",level:1,offensive:"No"}}},{node:{id:"C:/Users/slyon/Documents/GitHub/rots-site/src/pages/docs/skills/swipe.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:"<p>The Swipe skill allows you to make an additional attack with your\noffhand. The skill heavily depends on how good your warrior training\nis.</p>",frontmatter:{title:"SWIPE",syntax:"N/A (automatic effect)",group:"Warrior",level:1,offensive:"Yes"}}},{node:{id:"C:/Users/slyon/Documents/GitHub/rots-site/src/pages/docs/skills/twohanded.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:'<p>The Two-Handed skill helps with wielding weapons with both hands\nsuccessfully.  You can wield any weapon in one or two hands with the\ncommands "onehanded" and "twohanded" ("one and "two" being the shortcuts).\nSome weapons are worse onehanded, while some are worse twohanded.\nWhen wielding weapons twohanded, though, your effective skill is about\nthe average between your skill with the weapon\'s type and your skill\nin two-handed weapons.</p>',frontmatter:{title:"TWO-HANDED",syntax:null,group:"Warrior",level:1,offensive:"No"}}},{node:{id:"C:/Users/slyon/Documents/GitHub/rots-site/src/pages/docs/skills/weaponmastery.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:"<p>The Weapon Mastery skill gives you knowledge in all weapon types\nand the two-handed skill.  It is quite hard to learn, but easier than\nall of the skill separately.</p>",frontmatter:{title:"WEAPON MASTERY",syntax:"N/A (automatic effect)",group:"Warrior",level:1,offensive:"Yes"}}},{node:{id:"C:/Users/slyon/Documents/GitHub/rots-site/src/pages/docs/skills/kick.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:"<p>The Kick skill makes an attempt to kick chosen target, causing a small\namount of damage.  The success of a kick depends on how well you are learned\nin the skill, and your warrior level.  There is also a small delay after\nkicking, along with the normal waiting time before.</p>",frontmatter:{title:"KICK",syntax:"kick <target>",group:"Warrior",level:2,offensive:"Yes"}}},{node:{id:"C:/Users/slyon/Documents/GitHub/rots-site/src/pages/docs/skills/rescue.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:"<p>The Rescue skill allows one to rescue a target from a battle,\nreplacing the target in combat with you.  It only works against\none enemy, though, and it does not work at all for mental combat.</p>",frontmatter:{title:"RESCUE",syntax:"rescue <target>",group:"Warrior",level:3,offensive:"Yes"}}},{node:{id:"C:/Users/slyon/Documents/GitHub/rots-site/src/pages/docs/skills/bash.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:"<p>The Bash skill allows one to bash mobs/players, or doors.</p>\n<p>To bash a person is an attempt to knock them over.  If you succeed\nyou will inflict minor damage, and cause the victim to topple.  The\nvictim will be unable to do anything for a short while.  The success\nof a bash depends on how well you are learned in the skill, your\nwarrior level, your offensive abilities, your weight, and whether you\nwear a shield or not.</p>\n<p>To bash a door is an attempt to bash the door in, breaking it open.\nYour strength and bashing skill are depended on for success.  Dwarves, Beornings, Olog-Hais,\nand Uruk-Hais have a slight bonus, and Elves and Hobbits cannot\nbash doors at all.  Not all doors can be bashed, for example, gates\nand magical doors.</p>",frontmatter:{title:"BASH",syntax:"bash <target/door>",group:"Warrior",level:5,offensive:"Yes"}}},{node:{id:"C:/Users/slyon/Documents/GitHub/rots-site/src/pages/docs/skills/berserk.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:"<p>Berserk helps warriors control themselves while using berserk\ntactics.  This skill is necessary for effective use of berserk tactics.\nIt also helps warriors to calm down when they need to.</p>",frontmatter:{title:"BERSERK",syntax:"N/A (automatic effect)",group:"Warrior",level:7,offensive:"No"}}},{node:{id:"C:/Users/slyon/Documents/GitHub/rots-site/src/pages/docs/skills/bite.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:"<p>The Bite skill makes an attempt to bite the chosen target, causing a\nsmall amount of damage. The success of a bite depends on how well you are\nlearned in the skill, and your warrior level. There is a small delay after\nbiting to the target and the player, along with the normal waiting time\nbefore.</p>",frontmatter:{title:"BITE",syntax:"bite <target>",group:"Warrior",level:9,offensive:"Yes"}}},{node:{id:"C:/Users/slyon/Documents/GitHub/rots-site/src/pages/docs/skills/maul.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:"<p>The Maul skill makes an attempt to maul the chosen target, causing a\nsmall amount of damage. Maul will also apply a debuff to the target of\n-5 dodge, and apply a buff to the Beorning reducing the amount of\nphysical damage they take, this stacks up to five times. The success\nof maul depends on how well you are learned in the skill, and your\nwarrior level. The use of this skill has a move cost to it.</p>",frontmatter:{title:"MAUL",syntax:"maul <target>",group:"Warrior",level:12,offensive:"Yes"}}},{node:{id:"C:/Users/slyon/Documents/GitHub/rots-site/src/pages/docs/skills/findweakness.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:"<p>The Find Weakness skill allows you to find weaknesses in your\nenemy's defence.  If successful, it gives you additional damage\nwith your hits.  The skill heavily depends on how good your warrior\ntraining is.</p>",frontmatter:{title:"FIND WEAKNESS",syntax:"N/A (automatic effect)",group:"Warrior",level:20,offensive:"Yes"}}},{node:{id:"C:/Users/slyon/Documents/GitHub/rots-site/src/pages/docs/skills/rend.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:"<p>The rend skill makes an attempt to rend the chosen target, causing a\nlarge amount of damage. Rend can only be used while the target is bashed\nand the success of rend depends on how well you are learned in the skill,\nand your warrior level. There is a small delay after rending, along with\nthe normal waiting time before.</p>",frontmatter:{title:"REND",syntax:"rend <target>",group:"Warrior",level:21,offensive:"Yes"}}}]}},pathContext:{}}}});
//# sourceMappingURL=path---docs-skills-ad19e9d211181fb5ae4b.js.map